info:
To add a border to an element, use the border-style CSS attribute. This attribute can be set to many values, such as solid, dotted, and dashed. <CODE><style>
#MyHeader{
border-style:solid;
}
</style></CODE>

To set a color for your border, use the border-color CSS attribute. For now, focus on setting this value to a built in CSS color. <CODE><style>
#MyHeader{
border-style:solid;
border-width:5px;
border-color:green;
}
</style></CODE>

openQuestions.explanation:
You can use the border-width CSS attribute to specify the width for a border. <CODE><style>
#MyHeader{
border-width:2px;
}
</style></CODE>

You can use the border-style CSS attribute to specify the style for a border. <CODE><style>
#MyHeader{
border-style:dashed;
}
</style></CODE>
